Following an alleged incident of racism at the Hoërskool Jan Viljoen in Randfontein a week ago, Gauteng Education MEC, Panyaza Lesufi returns to the school today. In addition to racism allegations at the school, a teacher has also been suspended after sexual harassment allegations were reported. eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones is following the story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Education MEC, Panyaza Lesufi returns to Hoërskool Jan Viljoen in Randfontein on Sunday following an alleged incident of racism at the school. Lesufi is expected to meet parents following a rained-out meeting on Thursday. WATCH: School Violence | Discussion | Fresh look at dealing with racism It is anticipated that he will provide a way forward for the school. Meanwhile, a teacher has also been suspended at the school after sexual harassment allegations were reported.